01:02:06.780 --> 01:02:14.640
And they said, we're interested in finding out something if you could find out for us,

01:02:14.720 --> 01:02:22.000
and that is, who in the government is looking at the wedge of the DNA chart that says other?

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:26.040
And I said, I have no idea.

01:02:26.660 --> 01:02:28.180
They said, well, could you find out?

01:02:28.980 --> 01:02:32.540
Well, Linda Moulton Howe is a good friend of mine.

01:02:33.100 --> 01:02:37.280
And so I said, maybe Linda could answer the question.

01:02:37.920 --> 01:02:38.360
She knew.

01:02:40.140 --> 01:02:42.480
You talk about an investigative reporter.

01:02:43.060 --> 01:02:44.620
She's an investigative reporter.

01:02:44.620 --> 01:02:45.100
She knows.

01:02:45.640 --> 01:02:49.040
And she clicked off the names immediately.

01:02:50.220 --> 01:02:54.540
And so I asked them why.

01:02:55.540 --> 01:03:06.300
And he said, back centuries and centuries ago, when the ETs left the Earth, they took humans

01:03:06.300 --> 01:03:07.300
with them as slaves.

01:03:07.300 --> 01:03:16.100
And he said, we've been slaves for hundreds of generations on another planet.

01:03:16.680 --> 01:03:19.960
Our DNA has changed to match that.

01:03:20.520 --> 01:03:29.600
And he said, now that we're coming back here and serving to do the work at these bases, some

01:03:29.600 --> 01:03:30.620
of us are escaping.

01:03:30.620 --> 01:03:36.220
And he said, we don't want to do anything in the government.

01:03:36.440 --> 01:03:37.420
We don't want any power.

01:03:37.580 --> 01:03:38.300
We don't know anything.

01:03:38.520 --> 01:03:40.440
We just want to be free.

01:03:41.260 --> 01:03:42.520
That's all we want.

01:03:43.600 --> 01:03:47.740
And he said, we're afraid of that DNA test.

01:03:49.040 --> 01:03:53.520
Are those beings physiologically exactly the same as all other humans?

01:03:53.540 --> 01:03:54.420
These two guys were.

01:03:54.420 --> 01:04:00.800
Do they have any other sort of adaptive powers, behaviors, or traits based on their evolution?

01:04:00.800 --> 01:04:02.040
There were two guys in a parking lot.

01:04:02.380 --> 01:04:07.120
I don't know if it's true or not, but that's what happened.

01:04:08.340 --> 01:04:13.580
And so I guess it's a possibility of being true.

01:04:13.780 --> 01:04:14.240
I don't know.

01:04:14.240 --> 01:04:22.780
So those aliens that came here, you know, thousands of years ago, stories of like Anunnaki and

01:04:22.780 --> 01:04:24.300
watchers and that sort of thing.

01:04:24.420 --> 01:04:25.440
Something like that.

01:04:25.560 --> 01:04:31.960
So they had, you know, humans working for them when they came originally, you know, call

01:04:31.960 --> 01:04:33.720
it 10,000-ish years ago.

01:04:33.860 --> 01:04:36.120
And when they left, they took workers with them.

01:04:36.400 --> 01:04:37.720
They took workers with them.

01:04:37.800 --> 01:04:42.820
And then now they come back, occasionally visit some of these bases, and they bring the

01:04:42.820 --> 01:04:44.120
workers with them to work.

01:04:44.180 --> 01:04:44.900
To do the work.

01:04:45.000 --> 01:04:46.020
To do the slave work.

01:04:46.020 --> 01:04:49.060
And then occasionally some of those workers escape.

01:04:49.060 --> 01:04:52.220
That's what these two guys told me.

01:04:53.660 --> 01:04:56.340
Whether it's true or not, I don't know.

01:04:56.440 --> 01:04:57.760
That's just what they told me.

01:04:58.100 --> 01:05:02.580
But they told me in a way that I tended to believe it.

01:05:02.700 --> 01:05:03.560
I have no proof.

01:05:04.240 --> 01:05:10.700
Pat Price, who was originally responsible for viewing these four, you know, alien bases.

01:05:10.960 --> 01:05:11.220
Yeah.

01:05:11.220 --> 01:05:14.640
He was one of the most skilled remote viewers of all time.

01:05:14.900 --> 01:05:15.920
He was a psychic.

01:05:17.100 --> 01:05:18.580
How would you make that distinction?

01:05:19.320 --> 01:05:28.240
A psychic is a person who has the natural ability and great strength and knows how to

01:05:28.240 --> 01:05:28.900
access it.

01:05:29.300 --> 01:05:31.240
A remote viewer is trained.

01:05:31.560 --> 01:05:32.520
A remote viewer.

01:05:33.560 --> 01:05:34.700
A psychic is born.

01:05:35.240 --> 01:05:35.620
Yeah.

01:05:35.880 --> 01:05:36.200
Okay.

01:05:37.300 --> 01:05:42.760
The remote viewing that was made for the military wasn't made for psychics.

01:05:43.420 --> 01:05:45.420
The military didn't want psychics.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:52.280
They wanted to teach the ordinary soldier how to know what's over the hill and where to

01:05:52.280 --> 01:05:52.920
point the guns.

01:05:53.760 --> 01:05:54.540
That's what they wanted.

01:05:54.840 --> 01:05:56.380
Are you a remote viewer or a psychic?

01:05:56.660 --> 01:05:57.560
I'm a remote viewer.

01:05:57.560 --> 01:06:04.240
Well, but I grew up with the PK ability and some psychic sense.

01:06:04.840 --> 01:06:08.620
Everybody has intuition to some extent, okay?

01:06:09.600 --> 01:06:11.900
Some more than others and all that.

01:06:12.540 --> 01:06:19.220
But the controlled remote viewing is actually a martial art.

01:06:19.220 --> 01:06:25.100
But what happens is your subconscious knows something.

01:06:26.400 --> 01:06:32.540
It can't talk to the conscious mind without a psychiatrist's couch, you know.

01:06:33.040 --> 01:06:37.380
And so it gives you a physical response.

01:06:38.440 --> 01:06:46.440
When you can learn consciously to read those physical responses and you can train those to

01:06:46.440 --> 01:06:56.320
where it's a communication line, then you can physically pass a question to your subconscious

01:06:56.320 --> 01:06:56.960
mind.

01:06:57.240 --> 01:06:59.500
It will cause a physical response.

01:06:59.620 --> 01:07:02.080
You read that physical response and you've got the answer.

01:07:03.140 --> 01:07:05.220
That's what controlled remote viewing is.

01:07:05.340 --> 01:07:06.700
It's actually a martial art.

01:07:08.440 --> 01:07:08.920
Fascinating.

01:07:09.180 --> 01:07:09.360
Yeah.

01:07:09.360 --> 01:07:16.740
So it's not, oh, the answer is, you know, the answer is, put the question to your forehead

01:07:16.740 --> 01:07:18.480
and the answer is, it's not that at all.

01:07:18.980 --> 01:07:23.740
Do you have a sense of how it mechanically works or are we sort of in the stone age as

01:07:23.740 --> 01:07:28.700
far as, you know, with like a radio signal, it's pretty clear how it works with remote

01:07:28.700 --> 01:07:29.000
viewing.

01:07:29.360 --> 01:07:32.160
Do we understand the actual transmission mechanism?

01:07:32.160 --> 01:07:41.120
Well, some of the people who do the controlled remote viewing will write down the coordinates

01:07:41.120 --> 01:07:44.040
because you never tell them what the target is.

01:07:44.160 --> 01:07:51.440
You just give them an encrypted number and let their pen do scribble, scribble, scribble,

01:07:51.680 --> 01:07:54.000
and then they go back and touch it.

01:07:54.820 --> 01:07:59.900
Well, scribble, scribble, scribble is automatic writing, which some people are good at.

01:07:59.900 --> 01:08:05.620
Well, psychometry is where you go back and touch something and get information off of

01:08:05.620 --> 01:08:06.680
it, okay?

01:08:07.260 --> 01:08:10.640
And so that's one way to begin a CRV session.

01:08:12.360 --> 01:08:21.380
Another way, and the way that I teach my students, is the martial art way, wax on, wipe

01:08:21.380 --> 01:08:22.000
off, okay?

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:31.740
And so you say, draw me the most basic graphic you can of land, and some people will make

01:08:31.740 --> 01:08:39.000
a mountain, some people will make a straight line, and then show me water, and they'll

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:39.860
make a wavy line.

01:08:40.320 --> 01:08:45.780
And you have this other vocabulary, and you practice and practice and practice that.

01:08:45.780 --> 01:08:48.200
This is how they taught me.

01:08:48.700 --> 01:08:51.480
The Ingo Swann Method was taught to me.

01:08:52.400 --> 01:09:02.260
And when it gets to the point where the monitor who's calling out these words starts to say

01:09:02.260 --> 01:09:09.000
the word, and the viewer automatically makes the word that's going to be said, that's when

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:13.300
you know their subconscious mind is accessing the monitor.

01:09:13.300 --> 01:09:15.600
That's when you know you've got it.

01:09:16.740 --> 01:09:21.140
So then you go to what's, that's called stage one.

01:09:22.020 --> 01:09:26.920
So then you go to stage two, where you say, oh, describe the water.

01:09:28.460 --> 01:09:34.140
And by describing the water, you say, how does it taste?

01:09:34.760 --> 01:09:36.180
How does it feel?

01:09:36.400 --> 01:09:37.560
What's the temperature?

01:09:37.560 --> 01:09:46.340
You use only physical descriptors, and you get the physical descriptors of it, and then

01:09:46.340 --> 01:09:48.480
you say, oh, it feels cold.

01:09:49.420 --> 01:09:51.320
Well, how cold is it?

01:09:51.520 --> 01:09:53.340
That's where you start getting the measurements.

01:09:54.080 --> 01:10:02.380
And as you go through the six stages, you finally get down to where you can reproduce the

01:10:02.380 --> 01:10:03.820
circuitry on a circuit board.

01:10:03.820 --> 01:10:06.640
And I mean, it gets that detailed.

01:10:07.140 --> 01:10:10.260
And this is the genius of what Ingo Swann did.

01:10:10.860 --> 01:10:16.320
He started out with, I don't know what's at the target, but man, there's land and water

01:10:16.320 --> 01:10:17.680
and something man-made.

01:10:19.160 --> 01:10:19.840
You know?

01:10:19.840 --> 01:10:26.800
And at that point in the training, where you're in stage one training, you open the envelope

01:10:26.800 --> 01:10:31.640
and there's a ship sitting at dock, just like that, you know?

01:10:31.880 --> 01:10:39.100
And when you get good at that, 80% accurate at it through practice, then you move into stage

01:10:39.100 --> 01:10:39.420
two.

01:10:39.420 --> 01:10:48.900
Joseph McMonigle was tasked with remote viewing Mars a million years ago, claimed to see people

01:10:48.900 --> 01:10:55.160
who were much taller than human beings and pyramid structures and sort of a civilization.

01:10:55.780 --> 01:10:57.300
Have you seen anything like that?

01:10:57.360 --> 01:10:58.640
Have you ever remote viewed Mars?

01:10:58.640 --> 01:11:13.320
In stage six, there's a phenomenon called bilocation, and there's one step beyond that, which we

01:11:13.320 --> 01:11:15.540
call perfect site integration.

01:11:15.540 --> 01:11:22.820
When you reach that stage, you're not at the target, okay?

01:11:23.820 --> 01:11:30.120
But your attention is so focused on the target that you forget about the room around you or

01:11:30.120 --> 01:11:37.620
anything else, and your attention is so focused on it, you cannot tell that you're not at the

01:11:37.620 --> 01:11:37.940
target.

01:11:38.500 --> 01:11:42.640
You feel the breeze on your face, you feel the temperature, everything.

01:11:42.980 --> 01:11:43.660
You see it.

01:11:43.660 --> 01:11:53.120
And the first time that happened to me was with the Sedona region at Mars, and I was working

01:11:53.120 --> 01:11:53.520
along.

01:11:53.820 --> 01:12:00.680
I'd gotten some coordinates, just some numbers, and I was working along, and all of a sudden,

01:12:01.180 --> 01:12:04.080
I felt sand under my feet.

01:12:05.120 --> 01:12:07.560
Now, here's an idiosyncrasy.

01:12:08.440 --> 01:12:10.680
I never remote view with my shoes on.

01:12:11.540 --> 01:12:12.360
I don't know why.

01:12:12.360 --> 01:12:15.180
I'm a Texas boy.

01:12:15.280 --> 01:12:16.740
I take my shoes off, you know.

01:12:17.240 --> 01:12:26.000
And so I felt the sand under my feet, and I looked down, and there was, I was in a hallway

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:27.400
that was filled with sand.

01:12:28.520 --> 01:12:33.920
And I looked up, and there was an opening at the far end of the hallway.

01:12:33.920 --> 01:12:43.380
So I walked down to the opening, and I, it was open, so I leaned out, and the building that

01:12:43.380 --> 01:12:49.180
I was in was sloping backwards, and it was just all rough and just eroded and everything

01:12:49.180 --> 01:12:49.600
else.

01:12:49.600 --> 01:12:56.200
And I looked out, and I looked out, and the sun was dim, the sky was the wrong color.

01:12:56.840 --> 01:12:58.600
It was extremely cold.

01:12:58.900 --> 01:13:01.080
The place smelled bad.

01:13:01.080 --> 01:13:13.220
And I looked at the other things that were around, and came back and described them, and, you

01:13:13.220 --> 01:13:14.740
know, drew a picture of it and all that.

01:13:14.740 --> 01:13:25.900
And so I guess about six months later, we were out at a place in California visiting Hal Puthoff,

01:13:26.600 --> 01:13:33.540
and there was a picture on the wall of the Sedona region of Mars.

01:13:33.540 --> 01:13:40.080
And this was not the picture everybody sees.

01:13:40.300 --> 01:13:44.180
You know how the picture they show is all fuzzy and all?

01:13:45.080 --> 01:13:45.780
Come on.

01:13:46.440 --> 01:13:51.620
They can read your license plate from 250 miles through air.

01:13:52.680 --> 01:13:57.880
You're going to tell me they can't see a mountain sharply on Mars.

01:13:57.880 --> 01:14:06.920
And this was a very sharp picture, and there on the side of one of those pyramids, there's

01:14:06.920 --> 01:14:07.680
a little opening.

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:10.460
Been there, done that, didn't get the T-shirt.

01:14:12.180 --> 01:14:20.060
But I was looking at this picture and realizing that everything I had drawn from that angle

01:14:20.060 --> 01:14:25.420
from above was in the right place, everything.

01:14:25.420 --> 01:14:32.960
Everything, the sky that I saw was the color of the sky on Mars.

01:14:33.880 --> 01:14:38.580
The sun was dimmer, you know, and further away and all that.

01:14:38.980 --> 01:14:41.460
And the bitter cold and everything else.

01:14:41.680 --> 01:14:42.140
Was it red?

01:14:42.920 --> 01:14:43.680
What, the sun?

01:14:44.020 --> 01:14:44.660
The landscape.

01:14:45.460 --> 01:14:46.800
Oh, yeah, yeah, uh-huh.

01:14:47.020 --> 01:14:51.960
Yeah, it was orangish red, yeah, and all that.

01:14:52.020 --> 01:14:53.000
I mean, it was desert.

01:14:53.840 --> 01:14:54.620
It was sand.

01:14:54.620 --> 01:14:57.820
And after that session, they said, oh, you were on Mars.

01:14:59.100 --> 01:15:00.360
And I said, oh, okay.

01:15:01.060 --> 01:15:09.580
But when I saw that picture, that's when I realized, hey, I was on Mars.

01:15:11.560 --> 01:15:17.060
And, you know, I cannot say I've ever been physically on Mars.

01:15:17.060 --> 01:15:26.240
But I have had the experience, the real experience, of walking through the sands of Mars.

01:15:27.200 --> 01:15:29.740
And how are you going to explain that to anybody?

01:15:30.300 --> 01:15:32.100
I've had the experience of it.

01:15:32.540 --> 01:15:34.340
Did you see any alien life?

01:15:34.340 --> 01:15:43.160
Actually, I did, yeah, because the monitor took me elsewhere after that.

01:15:43.420 --> 01:15:44.060
But, yeah, mm-hmm.

01:15:44.880 --> 01:15:48.440
And so where did you go after that, where you saw alien life?

01:15:48.440 --> 01:15:51.460
Down into the pyramid.

01:15:51.460 --> 01:16:08.040
And it was beings that are much larger than humans, but with atrophied limbs, probably incapable of ever coming out, you know.

01:16:08.040 --> 01:16:09.860
What did they look like?

01:16:09.960 --> 01:16:11.960
Did they look like humans, but atrophied?

01:16:12.120 --> 01:16:12.340
No.

01:16:12.640 --> 01:16:15.840
Well, right at first, they looked to me like worms.

01:16:16.280 --> 01:16:25.780
I mean, their legs and their arms were just, you know, were there, but just, like I say, atrophied, not even used.

01:16:26.300 --> 01:16:29.200
Was their skin color the same color as humans?

01:16:29.200 --> 01:16:33.720
Oh, roughly, I think, yeah, as I remember it.

01:16:34.740 --> 01:16:37.520
I was there a very short time, and they pulled me out.

01:16:39.800 --> 01:16:40.200
Fascinating.

01:16:40.420 --> 01:16:40.660
Yeah.

01:16:40.840 --> 01:16:45.960
Did you get the sense as to whether they had a relationship with mankind at all, or they were from?

01:16:46.340 --> 01:16:46.860
I didn't.

01:16:46.940 --> 01:16:47.700
They pulled me out.

01:16:48.040 --> 01:16:49.600
They pulled me out from that, yeah.

01:16:50.040 --> 01:16:51.620
And this was present Mars.

01:16:51.780 --> 01:16:52.960
This isn't a million years ago.

01:16:53.040 --> 01:16:53.700
Present, yeah.

01:16:53.700 --> 01:16:58.080
What's the most exotic place you've bi-located to?

01:16:58.560 --> 01:16:59.700
The most exotic?

01:16:59.880 --> 01:17:01.140
I haven't heard that one before.

01:17:02.660 --> 01:17:06.060
The strangest place was Titan.

01:17:09.360 --> 01:17:14.680
I was tasked, for some reason, with Titan to find any life there.

01:17:15.060 --> 01:17:16.760
Titan is a moon of Jupiter?

01:17:17.120 --> 01:17:17.600
Yeah.

01:17:17.600 --> 01:17:24.700
And I found these two beings in a cave.

01:17:25.840 --> 01:17:31.800
Now, what I think they were looking for was sea under the surface or something like that.

01:17:32.360 --> 01:17:34.340
They weren't satisfied with what I got.

01:17:35.040 --> 01:17:39.300
But these two beings were conversing with each other.

01:17:39.300 --> 01:17:46.440
And, like I say, my forte is mental access.

01:17:46.440 --> 01:17:57.200
I have never, in any other time, found anything as totally alien as that.

01:17:57.600 --> 01:18:00.040
There was no understanding their thoughts.

01:18:00.600 --> 01:18:05.720
There was no understanding anything about them.

01:18:05.720 --> 01:18:07.460
I could tell they were thinking.

01:18:07.680 --> 01:18:08.780
I could hear their thoughts.

01:18:09.460 --> 01:18:12.320
And there was no translation.

01:18:12.740 --> 01:18:14.180
There was no nothing.

01:18:14.400 --> 01:18:18.640
The most alien thing I've ever experienced, period.

01:18:19.380 --> 01:18:21.660
And, you know, I've been tasked with a lot of aliens.

01:18:22.580 --> 01:18:28.100
This was just indescribably alien.

01:18:28.100 --> 01:18:30.560
Just completely foreign.

01:18:31.380 --> 01:18:31.780
Completely.

01:18:32.320 --> 01:18:34.080
Totally un-understandable.

01:18:34.780 --> 01:18:35.180
Incomprehensible.

01:18:35.860 --> 01:18:36.720
Incomprehensible, yeah.

01:18:37.400 --> 01:18:44.140
When you relay these things to your superiors as part of the remote viewing program, what do they say?

01:18:44.460 --> 01:18:45.240
Are they shocked?

01:18:45.360 --> 01:18:47.580
Or are they like, oh, just another day on the job?

01:18:47.640 --> 01:18:49.060
And they're very fausé about it?

01:18:49.200 --> 01:18:56.160
Oh, generally just another day on the job after, you know, like I say, they've been there for 10 years before I ever got there.

01:18:56.160 --> 01:18:59.880
So, you know, for them, it's just another day on the job, yeah.

01:19:00.100 --> 01:19:04.800
How many alien species do you think you've personally come into contact with?

01:19:05.640 --> 01:19:06.440
I think five.

01:19:06.940 --> 01:19:11.340
Have you seen any in a non-remote viewing capacity?

01:19:13.320 --> 01:19:14.860
I was afraid you were going to answer that.

01:19:15.080 --> 01:19:15.680
Ask that.

01:19:16.240 --> 01:19:16.720
Yes.

01:19:16.900 --> 01:19:18.140
And I can't talk about it.

01:19:18.440 --> 01:19:19.060
Why not?

01:19:19.260 --> 01:19:21.840
Because it was on a mission that I can't talk about.

01:19:22.180 --> 01:19:22.600
Okay.

01:19:23.280 --> 01:19:23.720
Whoa.

01:19:24.000 --> 01:19:24.380
Yeah.

01:19:24.580 --> 01:19:25.400
That's interesting.

01:19:26.100 --> 01:19:26.800
I'm sorry.

01:19:27.100 --> 01:19:27.860
No, it's okay.

01:19:28.120 --> 01:19:29.620
Is there anything you can share about it?

01:19:29.800 --> 01:19:30.120
No.

01:19:30.420 --> 01:19:30.720
Okay.

01:19:31.340 --> 01:19:32.100
Was it shocking?

01:19:32.860 --> 01:19:41.280
By that time, I had learned, anytime I went on one of these missions, I would always tell them,

01:19:41.280 --> 01:19:44.260
I don't want to know anything that I don't want to be responsible for.

01:19:44.600 --> 01:19:45.700
The alien was there.

01:19:45.700 --> 01:19:56.880
And so I immediately just looked away and kept going because I didn't want to be responsible

01:19:56.880 --> 01:19:58.480
for that, for knowing that.

01:19:58.480 --> 01:20:03.660
When you say mission, this isn't a remote viewing mission.

01:20:03.660 --> 01:20:05.380
This is like you were deployed somewhere?

01:20:06.100 --> 01:20:07.060
Somewhere else, yeah.

01:20:07.300 --> 01:20:07.700
Wow.

01:20:08.300 --> 01:20:08.480
Fascinating.

